import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['values'], bins='auto')
    plt.xlabel('Elevation Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of elevation values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    plt.axhline(y=avg_height, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average height of the volcano?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    width = data['width'][0]
    height = data['height'][0]
    values = np.array(data['values']).reshape(height, width)
    
    X = np.arange(0, width)
    Y = np.arange(0, height)
    X, Y = np.meshgrid(X, Y)
    
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = fig.gca(projection='3d')
    ax.plot_surface(X, Y, values, cmap='viridis')
    
    ax.set_title('What is the highest elevation point on the volcano?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
